# Survival Room

A fast-paced, top-down zombie survival shooter built with HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript. Fight off endless hordes of zombies, utilize power-ups, and see how long you can survive in the room!

**[Play the Live Demo!](https://your-github-username.github.io/your-repository-name/)** *(Replace the link above with your actual GitHub Pages URL after hosting.)*

![Gameplay Screenshot](https://placehold.co/600x400/2a2a2a/ff4500?text=Survival+Room+Gameplay)

---

## How to Play

The goal is to survive as long as possible against waves of zombies that grow stronger and more numerous over time.

* **Movement**: Use **WASD** or the **Arrow Keys** to move your character.
* **Aim**: Your character will automatically aim at your **mouse cursor**.
* **Attack**: **Left-click** to shoot your gun or swing your melee weapon.
* **Switch Weapons**: Use the **1** and **2** keys or the **scroll wheel** to switch between your pistol and axe.
* **Reload**: Press the **R** key to reload your pistol when you run out of ammo.
* **Pause**: Press the **P** key or the pause button in the top-right corner to pause the game.

---

## Features

* **Endless Waves**: Face increasingly difficult waves of zombies. How many can you beat?
* **Dual-Weapon System**: Strategically switch between a ranged pistol and a powerful melee axe.
* **Dangerous Power-ups**:
    * **Health Pack**: A green cross that restores you to full health. Appears for a limited time!
    * **Rage Pack**: A yellow bullet that grants your pistol unlimited ammo and a machine-gun fire rate for 5 seconds.
* **Environmental Hazards**: Starting from Wave 2, deadly bombs will spawn on the map. Avoid them at all costs!
* **Dynamic UI**: Keep track of your health, ammo, current wave, and score with a clean, responsive UI.
* **Savage Taunts**: If you die, the game will be sure to let you know how it feels about your performance.

---

## Local Setup

To run this game on your local machine, follow these simple steps:

1.  **Clone the repository:**
    ```sh
    git clone [https://github.com/your-github-username/your-repository-name.git](https://github.com/your-github-username/your-repository-name.git)
    ```

2.  **Navigate to the project directory:**
    ```sh
    cd your-repository-name
    ```

3.  **Open `index.html`:**
    Simply open the `index.html` file in any modern web browser (like Chrome, Firefox, or Edge).

That's it! The game will run locally in your browser.

---

## Technologies Used

* **HTML5**: For the core structure of the game.
* **CSS3**: For all styling, layout, and animations.
* **JavaScript (ES6+)**: For all game logic, from player movement to zombie AI and collision detection.
